    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Minerals that have assumed the shapes of the substances they have replaced; such as mineralized textiles in a burial environment formed through the replacement of the organic matrix of fiber with a largely inorganic one.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
